* Re: Noticed the EM1K0 GMD pule-by-pulse intensity disagrees with the average intensity --> SOLUTION
text: This problem was due to attenuation on electronics being too high. The signals should agree as long as the attenuation on the electronics (preattenuator for Electron 1 Amplifier) is set to 21 dB or less. This is the same way we typically unsaturate the gas detector so look here for panel locations: https://aosd.slac.stanford.edu/wiki/index.php/Gas_Detectors#Unsaturating_GMD All other attenuators on that panel should be set to zero.
